Explore Azure Cosmos DB
Key benefits
Azure Cosmos DB, a fully managed NoSQL database, offers several key benefits, including low latency, elastic scalability, defined data consistency, and high availability.
It supports global distribution, allowing databases to be placed close to users worldwide for reduced latency. With its multi-master replication protocol, every region supports
writes and reads, ensuring unlimited scalability and 99.999% availability globally. 

Azure Cosmos DB enables near real-time reads and writes across chosen regions, with automatic handling of data replication and high availability even in the event of regional outages.
Core Concepts (VERY IMPORTANT for exam)

1. 🌍 Global Distribution
	•	You can replicate data across multiple Azure regions
	•	Supports multi-master (multi-write) and single-write setups
	•	Helps with:
	•	High availability
	•	Disaster recovery

⸻

2. ⚡ Throughput (RU/s – Request Units)
	•	Everything costs RU/s (Request Units per second)
	•	Reads, writes, queries → all consume RU

👉 Example:
	•	Simple read → ~1 RU
	•	Complex query → higher RU

📌 Exam tip:
	•	If app is slow → increase RU/s
	•	If cost is high → optimize queries / indexing

⸻

3. 🧩 Partitioning (SUPER IMPORTANT)
	•	Data is split using a Partition Key

👉 Good partition key:
	•	High cardinality (many unique values)
	•	Even distribution

👉 Bad partition key:
	•	Causes hot partition (exam favorite ⚠️)

📌 Example:
	•	Good: userId
	•	Bad: country = Australia

⸻

4. 📦 Consistency Levels (Classic exam question)

5 levels (from strongest → weakest):
	1.	Strong
	2.	Bounded Staleness
	3.	Session ⭐ (default, MOST IMPORTANT)
	4.	Consistent Prefix
	5.	Eventual

📌 Trade-off:
	•	Strong consistency = lower performance
	•	Eventual = fastest but less accurate

⸻

5. 🔄 APIs Supported

Cosmos DB supports multiple models:
	•	Core (SQL API) ⭐ most used
	•	MongoDB API
	•	Cassandra API
	•	Table API
	•	Gremlin (graph)

⸻

6. 🧾 Indexing
	•	Automatic indexing by default
	•	Helps fast queries

📌 You can:
	•	Include/exclude fields
	•	Optimize RU consumption

⸻

7. 🔁 Change Feed
	•	Tracks changes in real-time
	•	Used for:
	•	Event-driven apps
	•	Azure Functions triggers

⸻

